# Component Standards

Every component in `src/lib/components/` must satisfy all three requirements below before it can be merged.

## 1 — Variant tests

Each component must have a `*.test.ts` co-located in its directory that:
- Imports the exported `tv()` variant function(s) from `index.ts`
- Asserts the correct Tailwind class is present for each variant key
- Uses `@testing-library/svelte` + `happy-dom` for components with no exported variant function

```ts
// ✅ GOOD — pure variant function test (no DOM needed)
import { dividerVariants } from './index.js';
test('dashed lineType adds border-dashed', () => {
  expect(dividerVariants({ lineType: 'dashed' })).toContain('border-dashed');
});

// ✅ GOOD — render test when no variant function is exported
import { render } from '@testing-library/svelte';
import Checkbox from './checkbox.svelte';
test('renders with border class', async () => {
  const { container } = render(Checkbox);
  expect(container.querySelector('button')?.className).toContain('border');
});
```

## 2 — Storybook story

Each component must have a corresponding story in `src/stories/`:
- A `ComponentNameStory.svelte` wrapper that exposes only explicitly modifiable props (no HTML attribute spread)
- A `component-name.stories.ts` with `tags: ['autodocs']`, `argTypes` typed with `control`, and at least one story per visible variant

## 3 — Tailwind presets

All visual styles must come from the design system tokens defined in `tailwind-presets/v4/theme.css`.

```ts
// ❌ BAD — arbitrary color not from the design system
'bg-[#0032A0]'

// ✅ GOOD — design system token
'bg-primary'
```

Never use inline `style=""` for colors, spacing, or typography. Use `tv()` variants with the project's tokens.
